<eesti>Arestimaja sisekorraeeskiri </eesti>
<inglise>Internal Rules of Detention House </inglise>
<eesti>Siseministri 1. detsembri 2000. a m&auml;&auml;rus nr 71 </eesti>
<inglise>Regulation No. 71 of the Minister of Internal Affairs of 1 December 2000 </inglise>
<eesti>(RTL 2000, 125, 2009), </eesti>
<inglise>(RTL (1) 2000, 125, 2009), </inglise>
<eesti>j&otilde;ustunud 15. detsembril 2000. a. </eesti>
<inglise>entered into force 15 December 2000. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;rus kehtestatakse "Vangistusseaduse" (RT I 2000, 58, 376; 72, &otilde;iend) paragrahvi 156 l&otilde;ike 5 alusel: </eesti>
<inglise>This Regulation is established on the basis of subsection 156 (5) of the Imprisonment Act (RT I 2000, 58, 376; 72, correction notice): </inglise>
<eesti>I peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 1 </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja sisekorraeeskirja rakendusala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of internal rules of detention house </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja sisekord t&auml;psustab vahistatu ja arestialuse "Vangistusseadusega" (RT I 2000, 58, 376; 72, &otilde;iend), "Kriminaalmenetluse koodeksiga" (ENSV &Uuml;T 1961, 1, 4 ja lisa; RT I 2000, 56, 369; 75, &otilde;iend; 84, 533; 86, 542) ja "Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikuga" (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 45 &otilde;iend; 58, 608; 60, 616; 87, 792; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40; 247; 49, 301 ja 305; 51, 321; 54, 346, 348 ja 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544 ja 548; 89, 578) kehtestatud kinnipidamise tingimusi ja korda politsei arestimajas (edaspidi arestimaja). </eesti>
<inglise>The internal rules of a detention house specify the conditions and procedure established by the Imprisonment Act (RT (2) I 2000, 58, 376; 72, correction notice), the Code of Criminal Procedure (ENSV &Uuml;T (3) 1961, 1, 4 and Appendix; RT I 2000, 56, 369; 75, correction notice; 84, 533; 86, 542) and the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 45 correction notice; 58, 608; 60, 616; 87, 792; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40; 247; 49, 301 and 305; 51, 321; 54, 346, 348 and 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544 and 548; 89, 578) for keeping detained persons and persons taken into custody in a police detention house (hereinafter detention house). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>M&auml;&auml;ruses kasutatavad m&otilde;isted </eesti>
<inglise>Definitions used in this Regulation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnik k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses on politseiametnik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, "officer" means a police officer. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teenistuja k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse t&auml;henduses on arestimaja koosseisuline teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) For the purposes of this Act, "staff member" means a staff member of a detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestialuse kohta s&auml;testatut kohaldatakse ka k&otilde;igile teistele arestimajas kinnipeetavatele isikutele, kui m&auml;&auml;ruses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Unless otherwise provided for in this Regulation, the provisions concerning detained persons apply to all other persons kept in custody in a detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuste eraldi hoidmise printsiip </eesti>
<inglise>Requirement of segregation of detained persons </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimajas hoitakse teistest arestialustest eraldi lisaks "Vangistusseaduse" paragrahvides 12 ja 90 nimetatud isikutele ka kainenemisele paigutatud isikuid ja v&auml;ljasaadetavaid. </eesti>
<inglise>In addition to persons specified in &sect;&sect; 12 and 90 of the Imprisonment Act, persons taken into custody to recover from intoxication and persons to be expelled from the county shall be segregated from other detained persons kept in a detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimajja lubamine </eesti>
<inglise>Permission to enter detention house </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimajja lubatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are permitted to enter a detention house: </inglise>
<eesti>1) prokur&ouml;r, seoses t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisega (k&otilde;ikidesse ruumidesse); </eesti>
<inglise>1) a prosecutor in connection with the performance of his or her official duties (access to all rooms); </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;iguskantsler (k&otilde;ikidesse ruumidesse); </eesti>
<inglise>2) the Legal Chancellor (access to all rooms); </inglise>
<eesti>3) politseiametnik, kes kontrollib arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml;d (k&otilde;ikidesse ruumidesse); </eesti>
<inglise>3) a police officer conducting an inspection of the work of the detention house (access to all rooms); </inglise>
<eesti>4) uurija (uurimistoimingu teostamiseks etten&auml;htud ruumi); </eesti>
<inglise>4) a preliminary investigator (access to the room prescribed for performing an investigative action); </inglise>
<eesti>5) arestimajja paigutatud isiku kaitsja (selleks etten&auml;htud kohtumisruumi); </eesti>
<inglise>5) the defence counsel of a person placed in the detention house (access to open visiting rooms prescribed for such purpose); </inglise>
<eesti>6) meditsiinit&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes on kutsutud arestimajja paigutatud isikule meditsiinilist abi osutama (eraldi ruumi v&otilde;i s&otilde;ltuvalt abivajaja seisundist kinnipidamiskambrisse); </eesti>
<inglise>6) the medical staff requested to provide medical care to a person placed in the detention house (a separate room or a cell, depending on the condition of the person in need of medical care); </inglise>
<eesti>7) tervisekaitsetalituse t&ouml;&ouml;taja, kes kontrollib arestimaja sanitaarset seisundit (k&otilde;ikidesse ruumidesse) v&otilde;i desinfitseerib ruume (desinfitseerimist vajavatesse ruumidesse); </eesti>
<inglise>7) an employee of the health protection office inspecting the sanitary conditions of the detention house (access to all rooms) or disinfecting the rooms (access to rooms to be disinfected); </inglise>
<eesti>8) isik, kes t&auml;idab t&ouml;&ouml;&uuml;lesandeid ning kellel on politseiprefekti sellekohane luba (loal m&auml;rgitud ruumidesse); </eesti>
<inglise>8) a person performing his or her official duties who has obtained corresponding permission from the police prefect (access to the rooms specified in the permission); </inglise>
<eesti>9) vaimulik (kohtumisruumi); </eesti>
<inglise>9) a minister of religion (access to the open visiting room); </inglise>
<eesti>10) Piinamise ja Ebainimliku v&otilde;i Alandava kohtlemise v&otilde;i Karistamise T&otilde;kestamise Euroopa Komitee liikmed (k&otilde;ikidesse ruumidesse); </eesti>
<inglise>10) members of the European Committee for the Prevention of Torture and Inhuman or Degrading Treatment or Punishment (access to all rooms); </inglise>
<eesti>11) konsulaart&ouml;&ouml;taja oma riigi kodaniku taotlusel (kohtumisruumi); </eesti>
<inglise>11) a consular officer, at the request of a citizen of the corresponding state (access to open visiting rooms); </inglise>
<eesti>12) isik, kes on lubatud kohtumisele (kohtumisruumi). </eesti>
<inglise>12) a person who has obtained a permission to visit (access to the open visiting rooms). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) L&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-9 nimetatud isikud lubatakse arestimajja t&ouml;&ouml;t&otilde;endi, punktis 10 nimetatud isikud Euroopa N&otilde;ukogu v&otilde;i kompetentse riigiasutuse poolt v&auml;ljastatud dokumendi, mis selgitab delegatsiooni liikmete isikud, nende &otilde;igused ja k&uuml;lastuse eesm&auml;rgi, punktis 11 nimetatud isik konsulaarpassi, punktis 12 nimetatud isik isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi esitamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Persons specified in clauses (1) 1) -9) are permitted to enter a detention house upon presentation of a certificate of employment; persons specified in clause 10) upon presentation of a document issued by the European Council or a competent state agency and which sets out the members of the delegation, their rights, and the purpose of the visit; persons specified in clause 11) upon presentation of their consular passport; and persons specified in clause 12) upon presentation of identification. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimajja paigutatud isiku kaitsja peab esitama advokaadi volikirja v&otilde;i dokumendi, mis kinnitab tema volitust esineda selle isiku kaitsjana (haldus&otilde;igusrikkumise menetluses order, kriminaalmenetluses volitus ja uurija v&otilde;i kohtu vastav luba). </eesti>
<inglise>The criminal defence counsel of a person placed in a detention house shall present an advocate's authorisation document or a document certifying his or her authority to act as the criminal defence counsel of the person (an order in the case of an administrative offence matter or a corresponding authorisation from a preliminary investigator or court in the case of a criminal matter). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimajja ei lubata k&otilde;rvalisi v&otilde;i ilmsete joobetunnustega isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Unauthorised persons or obviously intoxicated persons are not allowed to enter a detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>II peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter II </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku vastuv&otilde;tmine arestimajas </eesti>
<inglise>Admission of Persons to Detention House </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Dokumentide kontroll isiku vastuv&otilde;tmisel </eesti>
<inglise>Examination of documents upon admission </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja kontrollib isikut vastu v&otilde;ttes viimase arestimajja paigutamise aluseks olevaid dokumente ning isikut t&otilde;endavaid dokumente. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon admission of a person, an officer or staff member of a detention house shall examine the identity documents of the person and the documents on the basis which he or she is placed in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isiku arestimajja paigutamise aluseks olevad dokumendid on: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Documents on the basis of which a person can be placed in a detention house are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) isiku kahtlustatavana kinnipidamise protokoll; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the report concerning detention of a suspect; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kohtu m&auml;&auml;rus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a court ruling; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kohtu otsuse &auml;rakiri aresti v&otilde;i haldusaresti m&auml;&auml;ramise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a copy of a court judgment concerning imposition of detention or administrative detention; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kohtum&auml;&auml;ruse &auml;rakiri vahi alla v&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i v&auml;ljasaatmise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a copy of a court ruling on taking a person into custody or on expulsion of a person; </inglise>
<eesti>5) haldus&otilde;igusrikkumise protokoll, kui haldus&otilde;igusrikkumise eest v&otilde;ib kohaldada haldusaresti; </eesti>
<inglise>5) an administrative offence report if administrative detention can be imposed for the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>6) joobeseisundis isiku kainenema paigutamise protokoll; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a report on taking an intoxicated person into custody to recover from intoxication; </inglise>
<eesti>7) uurija v&otilde;i kohtu m&auml;&auml;rus sundtoomise kohaldamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>7) an order of a preliminary investigator or a court ruling on application of compelled attendance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui dokumendid on koostatud ebakorrektselt v&otilde;i puudulikult, siis isikut arestimajas vastu ei v&otilde;eta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If documents are incorrectly prepared or deficient, admission of the person to a detention house shall be refused. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestimajja vastuv&otilde;etav isik peab olema tuvastatud isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi v&otilde;i selle puudumise korral politsei koostatud isikusamasuse tuvastamise dokumendi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A person to be admitted to a detention house shall be identified on the basis of an identity document or, in the absence thereof, on the basis of an identification document prepared by the police. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja on p&otilde;hjendatult veendumusel, et isik ei ole tuvastatud, on tal &otilde;igus keelduda isikut vastu v&otilde;tmast ning n&otilde;uda isiku t&auml;iendavat tuvastamist. </eesti>
<inglise>If an officer or staff member of a detention house has good reason to believe that the identity of a person is not ascertained, he or she has the right to refuse to admit the person and to demand further identification of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud dokumentidele on vaja isiku vastuv&otilde;tmisel arestimajja esitada arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i teenistujale ka isiku kinnipidamise protokoll ning &otilde;iend isiku karistatuse kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In addition to the documents specified in subsection (2) of this section, a report on the detention of a person and a statement from the criminal record of the person shall be submitted to an officer or staff member of the detention house upon admission of the person to the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku vastuv&otilde;tmise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for admission of persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimajja paigutatavaid isikuid v&otilde;etakse vastu &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;ev l&auml;bi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons to be placed in a detention house shall be admitted at any time. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui korraga on toodud mitu isikut, paigutatakse nad kuni kaheks tunniks eraldi l&auml;biotsimiseks etten&auml;htud ruumidesse v&otilde;i sellise v&otilde;imaluse puudumise korral v&otilde;etakse isikud vastu arestimajja toomise j&auml;rjekorras. </eesti>
<inglise>If several persons arrive at one and the same time, they shall be placed in separate rooms intended for search for up to two hours or, in the absence of such rooms, shall be admitted to the detention house in the order of arrival. </inglise>
<eesti>Valve kuni vastuv&otilde;tmiseni kindlustab isiku toonud saatemeeskond. </eesti>
<inglise>The guard of a person until admission shall be ensured by the escort guard that brings the person to the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vastuv&otilde;etud isikute andmed kantakse arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse, kainenemisele toimetatud isiku andmed kainenemisele toimetatud isikute arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information concerning persons admitted to a detention house shall be entered in the work time journal of the detention house, and information concerning persons taken into custody to recover from intoxication shall be entered in the journal for recording persons taken into custody to recover from intoxication. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimajja vastuv&otilde;etavat isikut k&uuml;sitletakse tema terviseseisundi kohta ja tehakse tervisekontroll. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person to be admitted to a detention house shall be questioned about his or her state of health and shall undergo a medical examination. </inglise>
<eesti>Pedikuloosi (riide- v&otilde;i peat&auml;ide) olemasolu korral teostatakse sanitaarprotseduurid. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person suffers from pediculosis (has head or body lice), he or she shall be subjected to sanitary procedures. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vajadusel kutsutakse v&auml;lja kiirabi. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If necessary, emergency medical aid shall be called. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui isik toimetatakse haiglasse, informeeritakse sellest viivitamatult politseiprefektuuri korrapidajat, kes tagab valve korraldamise haiglas. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person is hospitalised, notice thereof shall be immediately given to the dispatcher of the police prefecture who shall ensure the guard of the person in the hospital. </inglise>
<eesti>Isikut, kes p&otilde;eb nakkus-, vaimu- v&otilde;i muud haigust, mis v&otilde;ib ohustada teda ennast, teiste arestialuste v&otilde;i arestimaja ametnike ja teenistujate tervist, arestimajja vastu ei v&otilde;eta. </eesti>
<inglise>A person suffering from an infectious disease, mental illness or any other disease which may be dangerous to the person himself or herself or to the health of other detained persons or the officers or staff members of a detention house shall not be admitted to the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>Selline isik suunatakse ravile haiglasse v&otilde;i vangla alalisse ravipunkti. </eesti>
<inglise>Such person shall be hospitalised or placed in the permanent medical treatment facility of a prison. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Tervisekontrolli ning vestlust isiku tervislikust seisundist viiakse l&auml;bi eraldi ruumis, milles samal ajal ei viibi teisi arestialuseid. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Medical examinations and conversations concerning the state of health of a person shall be conducted in a separate room where no other detained persons are present at the same time. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Arestimajja vastuv&otilde;etava isiku ning tema asjad otsib p&otilde;hjalikult l&auml;bi isikuga samast soost ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A person to be admitted a detention house and his or her personal belongings shall be thoroughly searched by an officer or staff member of the same sex as the person searched. </inglise>
<eesti>Ese ja aine, mida arestikambris ei tohi hoida, v&otilde;etakse arestimajja hoiule. </eesti>
<inglise>Items and substances which are prohibited in cells shall be deposited in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimajja hoiulev&otilde;etud asjade kohta koostatakse protokoll, mille &uuml;ks koopia pannakse arestialuse isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>Items deposited in a detention house shall be recorded in a report and a copy of the report shall be included in the personal file of the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Selgitatakse andmed isikute kohta, keda informeerida arestialuse ootamatu haiguse v&otilde;i muu vajaduse korral. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Information concerning persons to be notified in the case of a sudden illness or other emergency concerning a detained person shall be ascertained. </inglise>
<eesti>Andmed lisatakse arestialuse isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>Such information shall be included in the personal file of the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Identifitseerimisabin&otilde;ud </eesti>
<inglise>Measures of identification </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Fotografeerimist ja dakt&uuml;loskopeerimist ei tehta, kui isik tuuakse arestimajja vanglast ning tema isiklikus toimikus on vastavad dokumendid olemas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Photographing and fingerprinting shall not be performed if a person is brought to a detention house from a prison and his or her personal file contains the corresponding documents. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestimajja vastuv&otilde;etava isiku signaleetiliste fotode negatiive hoitakse arestialuse isiklikus toimikus koos fotode ja dakt&uuml;loskoopilise kaardiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The negatives of signaletic photographs of a person admitted to a detention house shall be included in the personal file of the detained person together with photographs and the fingerprint card. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Sisekorraeeskirja tutvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Overview of internal rules </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;etavale isikule tutvustatakse temale arusaadavas keeles ja viisil allkirja vastu arestimaja sisekorraeeskirja, tema &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi, p&auml;evakava ning antakse kirjalik teave nende kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>A person admitted to a detention house shall be given an oral overview of and written information concerning the internal rules of the detention house, his or her rights and obligations and the daily schedule of the detention house against signature in a language and manner which he or she understands. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Isiku tualett </eesti>
<inglise>Personal hygiene </inglise>
<eesti>Vastuv&otilde;etaval isikul v&otilde;imaldatakse end pesta. </eesti>
<inglise>A person admitted to a detention house shall be provided with an opportunity to wash. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui isik, kes on antisanitaarses seisundis ja see v&otilde;ib ohustada nii arestimajja paigutatava isiku enda kui ka teiste isikute tervist, keeldub end pesemast, siis v&otilde;ib isikut pesta sunniviisiliselt temaga samast soost ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person to be placed in a detention house is in an unhygienic condition and this may endanger his or her health or the health of other persons, but the person refuses to wash himself or herself, the person may be forcibly washed by an officer or staff member of the same sex as the person. </inglise>
<eesti>III peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter III </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnipidamine arestimajas </eesti>
<inglise>Detention in Detention Houses </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuste suhtlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Communication between detained persons </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja juht on kohustatud rakendama meetmeid, et v&auml;listada eri kambritesse paigutatud arestialuste omavaheline suhtlemine ja sidepidamine. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of a detention house is required to take measures to prevent communication between detained persons who are lodged in different cells. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>H&uuml;gieen arestimajas </eesti>
<inglise>Hygiene in detention houses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kambreid ning teisi ruume tuleb iga p&auml;ev koristada ning vajadusel puhastada desinfitseerivate vahenditega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Cells and other rooms shall be cleaned daily and, if necessary, with disinfectants. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestialusel v&otilde;imaldatakse kord n&auml;dalas kasutada sauna, du&scaron;&scaron;i v&otilde;i vanni ning vahetada voodipesu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Detained persons shall be provided with an opportunity to use a sauna, shower or bath and to change bed clothes once a week. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimajas kasutatavaid toidun&otilde;usid pestakse desinfitseerivate ainetega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The utensils used in a detention house shall be washed with disinfectants. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestialune kannab arestimajas isiklikke riideid ja vahistatu vanglast toomise korral vangla antud riietust. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In a detention house, detained persons wear their personal clothes and persons in custody who are brought from a prison wear the clothes provided by the prison. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja p&auml;evakava </eesti>
<inglise>The daily schedule of detention house </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Politseiprefekt kinnitab arestimaja p&auml;evakava, milles s&auml;testatakse arestialuste toitlustamise, &ouml;&ouml;rahu jm ajad ning kestus. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The daily schedule of a detention house providing the times and duration of the meals, rest time, etc. of detained persons shall be approved by the police prefect. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestimaja p&auml;evakava koostatakse nii, et arestialusele oleks tagatud v&auml;hemalt 8-tunnine pidev uneaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The daily schedule of a detention house shall be drawn up such as to ensure a minimum of eight hours of uninterrupted sleep time for detained persons. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Arstiabi arestimajas </eesti>
<inglise>Medical care in detention houses </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimaja ametnikul ja teenistujal on kohustus osutada arestialusele esmaabi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The officers and staff members of a detention house have the obligation to provide first aid to detained persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestimajas peab olema ametnikele ja teenistujatele k&auml;ttesaadav k&auml;siapteek. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Detention houses shall have first-aid kits accessible by the officers and staff members. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vajadusel, arestialuse haigestumise v&otilde;i surma korral kutsutakse arestimajja kiirabi, kes osutab abi kohapeal, toimetab haige ravile haiglasse v&otilde;i tuvastab surma, v&auml;ljastades sellekohase &otilde;iendi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If necessary, e.g. in the case of an illness or death of a detained person, the emergency medical aid shall be called to the detention house and the medical staff shall provide assistance on site, take the person to a hospital for treatment, or establish the fact of death of the person and issue a corresponding certificate. </inglise>
<eesti>Surnu toimetamiseks surnukuuri kutsutakse kohale vastav teenistus. </eesti>
<inglise>A corresponding service shall be called to transport a deceased person to a mortuary. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse tehakse asjaomane sissekanne. </eesti>
<inglise>A corresponding entry shall be made in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja informeerib viivitamatult arestialuse raskest haigestumisest, raviasutusse toimetamisest v&otilde;i surmast: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An officer or staff member of a detention house shall immediately notify the following persons of a serious illness, placement in a medical institution or death of a detained person: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kohut, uurijat v&otilde;i muud ametiisikut v&otilde;i ametiasutust, kelle m&auml;&auml;ruse v&otilde;i otsuse alusel isik arestimajja paigutati; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the court, preliminary investigator or other official or agency on the basis of whose ruling, order or decision the person was placed in the detention house; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tema omakseid v&otilde;i tema soovil m&otilde;nda teist isikut. </eesti>
<inglise>2) his or her immediate family or, at the request of the detained person, any other person. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja teeb m&auml;rke arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse informatsiooni edastamise aja ning informeeritud isiku andmete kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The officer or staff member of the detention house shall make a notation concerning the time of communication of such information and information concerning the persons notified in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ravimit, mida arestialusele on vaja manustada regulaarselt, v&otilde;idakse hoida arestimaja ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja valduses ning seda antakse isikule arsti ettekirjutuse kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Medicinal products which must be administered to a detained person on a regular basis may be kept in the possession of an officer or staff member of the detention house and the product is administered to the person pursuant to the doctor's prescription. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahistatu &uuml;mberpaigutamine teise kinnipidamiskohta </eesti>
<inglise>Relocation of person taken into custody to other custodial institution </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vahistatu v&otilde;ib &uuml;mber paigutada &uuml;hest arestimajast teise v&otilde;i kinnise vangla eelvangistusosakonda, kui seda on vaja eeluurimise huvides, julgeoleku kaalutlustel v&otilde;i n&otilde;uab seda prokur&ouml;r, kohtunik v&otilde;i uurija, kes menetleb kriminaalasja. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A person taken into custody may be relocated from one detention house to another or to a ward prescribed for custody pending trial in a maximum-security prison if this is necessary in the interests of preliminary investigation or for security reasons or if so required by the prosecutor, judge or preliminary investigator conducting the proceedings in the criminal matter. </inglise>
<eesti>Vahistatu &uuml;mberpaigutamisel saadetakse sinna ka vahistatu isiklik toimik ja hoiulev&otilde;etud asjad. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon relocation of a person in custody, his or her personal file and personal belongings shall also be sent to the new location. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Alaealine vahistatu v&otilde;idakse &uuml;mber paigutada vanglasse, et v&otilde;imaldada tal j&auml;tkata p&otilde;hi- v&otilde;i &uuml;ldkeskhariduse omandamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A minor taken into custody may be relocated in a prison in order to provide him or her with an opportunity to continue acquisition of basic education or general secondary education. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja juht teeb sellekohase ettepaneku eeluurimisega tegelevale isikule. </eesti>
<inglise>The head of the detention house shall make a corresponding proposal to the person conducting preliminary investigation. </inglise>
<eesti>IV peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter IV </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuse &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and Obligations of Detained Persons </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuse &otilde;igused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of detained persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialusel on &otilde;igus: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teada kinnipidamise p&otilde;hjust, enda &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) know the reason for the detention, and his or her rights and obligations; </inglise>
<eesti>2) saada korrap&auml;raselt ja toiduh&uuml;gieenile vastavat toitu vastavuses elanikkonna &uuml;ldiste toitumistavadega ning silmas pidades elutegevuseks vajalikku toidutarvet; </eesti>
<inglise>2) receive food on a regular basis and which is in compliance with the food hygiene requirements and the general dietary habits of the population such as to meet the food requirement necessary for survival; </inglise>
<eesti>3) saada arstiabi ning ravimeid, arsti ettekirjutusel dieettoitu; </eesti>
<inglise>3) receive medical care and medicinal products and, if so prescribed by a doctor, dietetic food; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juhul, kui teda hoitakse arestimajas kauem kui kolm &ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva, viibida v&otilde;imaluse ja soovi korral v&auml;rskes &otilde;hus valve all v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks tund p&auml;evas; </eesti>
<inglise>4) have an opportunity to stay in the open air under surveillance for at least one hour a day if possible and so requested by the detained person, if he or she is kept in a detention house for more than three days; </inglise>
<eesti>5) piiramatult kohtuda oma kaitsjaga segamatult ja vahetult; </eesti>
<inglise>5) meet his or her defence counsel directly and without interruption for an unlimited number of times; </inglise>
<eesti>6) segamatult kohtuda vaimulikuga; arestialusele v&otilde;imaldatakse vaimulikuga kohtuda &uuml;ks kord n&auml;dalas kuni kaks tundi; </eesti>
<inglise>6) meet a minister of religion without interruption; detained persons shall have the opportunity to meet a minister of religion once a week for up to two hours; </inglise>
<eesti>7) tutvuda isikliku toimikuga arestimaja ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja juuresolekul; </eesti>
<inglise>7) examine his or her personal file in the presence of an officer or staff member of the detention house; </inglise>
<eesti>8) omal kulul kirjavahetust pidada, samuti telefoni kasutada, kui arestimajas on selleks tehnilised tingimused; </eesti>
<inglise>8) have correspondence and use a telephone at his or her own expense if corresponding technical conditions are available in the detention house; </inglise>
<eesti>9) lugeda riigi p&auml;evalehti ja ajakirju ning raamatukogu olemasolu korral sealolevat kirjandust; </eesti>
<inglise>9) read daily national newspapers and national journals, and use the library if the detention house has a library; </inglise>
<eesti>10) hoida kambris kriminaal- v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;igusrikkumise asja menetlusega seoses olevaid dokumente ja m&auml;rkmeid; </eesti>
<inglise>10) store documents and notes relating to his or her criminal or administrative offence matter in the cell; </inglise>
<eesti>11) kohtuda j&auml;relevalve all oma perekonnaliikmete ja teiste isikutega l&auml;htuvalt arestimaja v&otilde;imalustest ja koosk&otilde;las seadusega; </eesti>
<inglise>11) under supervision and under the conditions available in the detention house and in compliance with law, meet his or her family members and other persons; </inglise>
<eesti>12) kord n&auml;dalas k&auml;ia saunas, vannis v&otilde;i du&scaron;i all ning saada voodipesu; </eesti>
<inglise>12) use a sauna, bath or shower and receive clean bed clothes once a week; </inglise>
<eesti>13) esitada politseiprefektuuri juhtkonnale suulisi v&otilde;i kirjalikke avaldusi ja kaebusi arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>13) submit oral or written petitions or complaints to the leadership of the police prefecture concerning the work of the detention house; </inglise>
<eesti>14) abikaasa, isa, ema, vanaisa, vanaema, lapse, lapsendaja, lapsendatu, venna v&otilde;i &otilde;e parandamatult raske haiguse v&otilde;i surma v&otilde;i muu erakorralise s&uuml;ndmuse korral vabaneda arestimaja juhi n&otilde;usolekul kuni kolmeks p&auml;evaks, kusjuures aresti kandmine peatub; </eesti>
<inglise>14) with the consent of the head of the detention house, be granted a leave of up to three days in the case of a terminal illness or the death of his or her spouse, father, mother, grandfather, grandmother, child, adoptive parent, adoptive child, brother or sister, or in case of other emergencies, whereas service of the detention shall be suspended for the duration of such leave; </inglise>
<eesti>15) tehnilise v&otilde;imaluse korral hoida arestimaja juhi loal kambris isiklikku raadiot ja televiisorit, kui nende kasutamine ei h&auml;iri teisi isikuid. </eesti>
<inglise>15) have a personal radio or television in the cell if allowed by the technical conditions and permitted by the head of the detention house and if the use of the radio or television does not disturb other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestialusel on &otilde;igus hoida kambris j&auml;rgmisi toiduaineid ja esemeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detained person has the right to keep the following foodstuffs and items in his or her cell: </inglise>
<eesti>1) leiva- ja saiatooteid, kuivi kondiitritooteid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) bread and dry pastry products; </inglise>
<eesti>2) soolakala, t&auml;issuitsuvorsti, termiliselt t&ouml;&ouml;deldud v&otilde;i soolaliha, rasvaineid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) salted fish, hard sausages, heat treated or salted meat, fats; </inglise>
<eesti>3) juustu, konserve (mitte klaas- ega metalltaaras), piimatooteid, kuivsuppe; </eesti>
<inglise>3) cheese, preserved food (except preserves in glass or metal containers), milk products, dehydrated soups; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juur- ja puuvilju, mahla (mitte klaas- ega metalltaaras); </eesti>
<inglise>4) vegetables, fruits and juices (except those in glass or metal cans); </inglise>
<eesti>5) halvaad, kompvekke (v&auml;lja arvatud karamell) ja mett; </eesti>
<inglise>5) halva, confectionery (except caramel) and honey; </inglise>
<eesti>6) &uuml;hte komplekti hooajalist &uuml;leriietust, peakatet, jalatseid; </eesti>
<inglise>6) one set of seasonal clothes, headwear and footwear; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kahte komplekti aluspesu, sukki-sokke, kindaid (k&uuml;lmal hooajal), taskur&auml;tte; </eesti>
<inglise>7) two sets of underwear, stockings or socks, gloves (in cold seasons), handkerchiefs; </inglise>
<eesti>8) tualetttarbeid (seep, hambahari, hambapasta, seebikarp, kamm, k&auml;ter&auml;tt, tualettpaber), elektri- v&otilde;i mehhaanilist pardlit; </eesti>
<inglise>8) toiletries (soap, toothbrush, toothpaste, soap box, comb, towel, toilet paper), an electric or mechanical shaver; </inglise>
<eesti>9) prille, prillitoosi, arsti ettekirjutusel proteese ja karke; </eesti>
<inglise>9) spectacles, a spectacle case, and prosthetic appliances or crutches if prescribed by a doctor; </inglise>
<eesti>10) suitsetamistarbeid, tubakatooteid, tikke, arsti ettekirjutusel ravimeid; </eesti>
<inglise>10) smoking appliances, tobacco products, matches, and medicinal products if prescribed by a doctor; </inglise>
<eesti>11) oma kriminaal- v&otilde;i haldus&otilde;igusrikkumise menetlust puudutavaid m&auml;&auml;rusi, otsuseid ja muid dokumente; </eesti>
<inglise>11) rulings, orders, decisions or other documents concerning his or her criminal or administrative offence matter; </inglise>
<eesti>12) kirjapaberit, &uuml;mbrikke, postmarke, kirjatarbeid ja &otilde;ppematerjale; </eesti>
<inglise>12) writing paper, envelopes, stamps, stationery and study materials; </inglise>
<eesti>13) ilukirjandust, ajalehti ja ajakirju (kuni viis eksemplari); </eesti>
<inglise>13) literature, newspapers and journals (up to five articles); </inglise>
<eesti>14) naisarestialusel h&uuml;gieenitarbeid, lokirulle, meikimisvahendeid, v&ouml;&ouml;d; </eesti>
<inglise>14) in the case of female detained persons, sanitary articles, curlers, cosmetics, belts; </inglise>
<eesti>15) valmistajatehase kehtestatud ohutusn&otilde;uetele vastavat vee kiirkeetjat (kuni 0,5 kW); </eesti>
<inglise>15) an electric kettle which meets the safety requirements established by the manufacturer (up to 0.5 kW); </inglise>
<eesti>16) malet, kabet, doominod (&uuml;ks komplekt); </eesti>
<inglise>16) chess, chequers or domino (one set); </inglise>
<eesti>17) plastn&otilde;usid, k&auml;ekella. </eesti>
<inglise>17) plastic utensils, a watch. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestialusel kaasas olevate ja arestimajja hoiule antud v&otilde;i v&otilde;etud esemete kogukaal ei tohi &uuml;letada 50 kilogrammi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The total weight of the personal belongings and items of a detained person deposited in the detention house shall not exceed 50 kilograms. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) L&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud esemeid v&otilde;ib arestialuselt &auml;ra v&otilde;tta, kui need ohustavad teiste arestimajas viibivate isikute elu v&otilde;i tervist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Items specified in subsection (2) may be taken away from a detained person if they are dangerous to the life or health of other persons present in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud esemetega toimimine </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibited items </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Esemed ja ained, mida ei tohi tsiviilk&auml;ibes v&otilde;i arestimajas hoida, v&otilde;etakse arestialuselt &auml;ra ning nendega toimitakse seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Items and substances which are not allowed in commerce or in the detention house shall be taken away from a detained person and handled pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Auml;rav&otilde;etud dokumendid j&auml;etakse hoiule arestimaja juhi k&auml;tte ning tagastatakse arestialusele tema vabastamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Confiscated documents shall be deposited with the head of the detention house and returned to the detained person upon his or her release. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vahistatu &uuml;mberpaigutamisel &uuml;hest arestimajast teise v&otilde;i vanglasse antakse sinna &uuml;le ka temalt hoiule v&otilde;etud esemed, ravimid, dokumendid jms. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a person held in custody is relocated from one detention house to another or to a prison, his or her deposited items, medicinal products, documents, etc., shall be transferred accordingly. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Raha, v&auml;&auml;rtesemed ja -paberid antakse esemete hoiule v&otilde;tmise protokolli alusel vastutavale hoiule politseiprefektuuri raamatupidamistalitusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Money, valuables and securities shall be deposited with the accounting division of a police prefecture on the basis of the report on depositing the items and the police prefecture shall be liable for such items. </inglise>
<eesti>Asjade hoiulev&otilde;tmise protokolli &uuml;ks koopia antakse arestialusele ja teine koopia paigutatakse tema isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>One copy of the report on depositing the items shall be given to the detained person and the other copy shall be included in his or her personal file. </inglise>
<eesti>Kainenema paigutatud isikule antakse nimetatud koopia p&auml;rast kainenemist. </eesti>
<inglise>A person taken into custody to recover from intoxication shall receive such copy after he or she has recovered. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuse kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of detained persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialune on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person is required: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;itma "Vangistusseaduse", arestimaja sisekorraeeskirja ja arestimaja p&auml;evakava n&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to comply with the requirements of the Imprisonment Act, the internal rules of the detention house and the daily schedule of the detention house; </inglise>
<eesti>2) alluma vastuvaidlematult arestimaja ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja seaduslikule korraldusele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to comply with the legal orders of the officers and staff members of the detention house without argument; </inglise>
<eesti>3) mitte takistama arestimaja ametnikul v&otilde;i teenistujal kohustuste t&auml;itmist ega h&auml;irima teisi arestialuseid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) not to prevent the officers or staff members of the detention house from the performance of their duties or disturb other detained persons; </inglise>
<eesti>4) viivitamatult teatama arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i teenistujale k&otilde;ikidest asjaoludest, mis v&otilde;ivad ohustada arestimaja julgeolekut, sisekorda v&otilde;i teise isiku elu v&otilde;i tervist; </eesti>
<inglise>4) to notify an officer or staff member of the detention house immediately of all circumstances which may endanger the security or internal procedure of the detention house or the life or health of other persons; </inglise>
<eesti>5) suhtuma heaperemehelikult tema valduses olevatesse esemetesse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) to handle the items in his or her possession prudently; </inglise>
<eesti>6) hoolitsema isikliku h&uuml;gieeni eest, olema korrastatud v&auml;limusega, hoidma puhtust kambris ja arestimaja teistes ruumides; </eesti>
<inglise>6) to maintain personal hygiene, look decent and maintain order in the cell and other rooms of the detention house; </inglise>
<eesti>7) hoidma arestimaja ruumides liikudes k&auml;ed selja taga. </eesti>
<inglise>7) to keep hands behind the back while moving around in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestialusel on keelatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detained person shall not: </inglise>
<eesti>1) rikkuda kambrikaaslaste v&otilde;i arestimaja rahu, pidada mis tahes vormis sidet teises kambris viibiva isikuga kirjavahetuse ja koputamise teel v&otilde;i muul viisil; </eesti>
<inglise>1) disturb the peace of his or her cell mates or the detention house or engage in any communication with persons in other cells either by way of correspondence or knocking or in any other manner; </inglise>
<eesti>2) takistada kambri j&auml;lgimist arestimaja ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja poolt; </eesti>
<inglise>2) prevent an officer or staff member of the detention house from observing his or her cell; </inglise>
<eesti>3) rikkuda kambrit v&otilde;i selle sisustust; </eesti>
<inglise>3) damage the cell or the furnishings thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;ngida varalise v&otilde;i muu kasu saamise eesm&auml;rgil; </eesti>
<inglise>4) gamble in order to receive proprietary or other benefits; </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&auml;toveerida ennast v&otilde;i kambrikaaslast; </eesti>
<inglise>5) tattoo himself or herself or his or her cell mates; </inglise>
<eesti>6) suitsetada, kui sellega ei n&otilde;ustu teine samas kambris viibiv isik; </eesti>
<inglise>6) smoke if other persons in the same cell are against it; </inglise>
<eesti>7) m&uuml;&uuml;a, kinkida v&otilde;i vahetada isiklikku eset v&otilde;i ainet. </eesti>
<inglise>7) sell, give as a present or exchange personal items or substances. </inglise>
<eesti>V peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter V </inglise>
<eesti>Pakkide saamise kord </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Receiving Packages </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>&Otilde;igus saada pakki </eesti>
<inglise>Right to receive packages </inglise>
<eesti>Vahistatul on &otilde;igus &uuml;ks kord n&auml;dalas saada k&auml;si- v&otilde;i postipakki kogukaaluga kuni viis kilogrammi. </eesti>
<inglise>Once a week, a person held in custody has the right to receive a package delivered by hand or by post and weighing a total of up to five kilograms. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;sipakkide vastuv&otilde;tu korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for receiving packages delivered by hand </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pakkide vastuv&otilde;tmine arestimajas korraldatakse v&auml;hemalt kahel p&auml;eval n&auml;dalas p&auml;evasel ja &otilde;htusel kellaajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Receipt of packages shall be organised in a detention house at least twice a week during daytime and in the evening. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Pakkide vastuv&otilde;tmise ruumis peab n&auml;htaval kohal olema lubatud esemete ja toiduainete nimekiri ning teave vastuv&otilde;turuumi t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse, pakkide vastuv&otilde;tmise korra ning vastutuse kohta nimetatud korra rikkumise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A list of permitted items and foodstuffs and information concerning the work schedule of the room intended for the receipt of packages, the procedure for receiving packages and liability for violation of the procedure shall be displayed in a visible place in the room intended for the receipt of packages. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;sipaki tooja esitab arestimajale vastavasisulise avalduse kahes eksemplaris. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person who delivers a package by hand shall submit a corresponding application in two copies to the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Paki vastuv&otilde;tmisel arestimajja kontrollib arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja selle sisu paki tooja juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The officer or staff member of a detention house who takes delivery a package shall examine the contents of the package in the presence of the deliverer. </inglise>
<eesti>Paki &uuml;leandmisel paki saajale toimub kontroll selle saaja juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>If a package is delivered directly to the recipient, the contents of the package shall be examined in the presence of the recipient. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Paki vastuv&otilde;tmisel allkirjastatakse pakitooja avaldus. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon taking delivery of a package, the application of the deliverer shall be signed. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse &uuml;ks eksemplar tagastatakse paki toojale. </eesti>
<inglise>One copy of the application shall be returned to the deliverer. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduse teisele eksemplarile annab paki saanud isik allkirja paki k&auml;ttesaamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>The recipient of the package shall certify receipt of the package by signing the other copy of the application. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaldus pannakse paki saaja isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>The application shall be included in the personal file of the recipient. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Paki saamise kohta teeb ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja sissekande arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestamise raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An officer or staff member of a detention house shall record the receipt of a package in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Pakis keelatud esemed </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibited items in packages </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Pakis ei tohi olla kasutusaega &uuml;letanud toiduainet, samuti ei ole soovitatav pakki panna kiiresti riknevat toiduainet (maasikad, kohupiim, keeduvorst, suitsukala jne). </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Packages shall not include foodstuffs the use-by date of which has expired; perishable food products (strawberries, curd cheese, cooked sausages, smoked fish, etc.) are also not recommended to be included in packages. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Toiduaine kontrollitakse enne selle &uuml;leandmist pakisaajale (leiva-, saiatoode, vorst, juust jm tahke aine t&uuml;keldatakse, vedelaine valatakse &uuml;mber teise n&otilde;usse v&otilde;i s&otilde;elutakse jms). </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Foodstuffs shall be examined before delivery to the recipient (bread, sausages, cheese and other hard substances shall be parcelled, liquid substances shall be poured into another dish or sieved, etc.) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Pakis ei tohi olla kirja ega sedelit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Packages shall not include letter or notes. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Paki tagastamise p&otilde;hjuste kohta teeb ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja sissekande arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An officer or staff member of a detention house shall record the reasons for non-acceptance of a package in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Postipakkide vastuv&otilde;tu korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for receiving packages delivered by post </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Postipakk v&otilde;etakse vastu ainult siis, kui paki saaja viibib selles arestimajas. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Packages delivered by post shall be accepted only if the recipient is held in custody in the corresponding detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Teise arestimajja v&otilde;i vanglasse paigutatud vahistatu nimele saabunud pakki vastu ei v&otilde;eta, kuid postiteenust osutavale ettev&otilde;tjale teatatakse tema uus aadress. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Packages delivered to the name of a person held in custody in another detention house or a prison shall not be accepted, but the undertaking providing the postal service shall be notified of the new address of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimajast vabastatud v&otilde;i surnud isiku nimele saabunud pakki vastu ei v&otilde;eta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Packages delivered to the name of a deceased person or a person released from the detention house shall not be accepted. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Postiteenust osutavale ettev&otilde;tjale teatatakse postipaki adressaadile &uuml;leandmata j&auml;tmise p&otilde;hjus. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The undertaking providing the postal service shall be notified of the reason for failure to deliver the package to the addressee. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Saadud postipakk avatakse ning vaadatakse l&auml;bi vahistatu juuresolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A package delivered by post shall be opened and examined in the presence of the person held in custody. </inglise>
<eesti>Pakist leitud ning vahistatule keelatud ese ja aine v&otilde;etakse &auml;ra ning koostatakse v&otilde;etuse protokoll. </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibited items or substances found in the package shall be confiscated and a report on seizure shall be prepared. </inglise>
<eesti>V&otilde;etud eseme, aine ja dokumendiga toimitakse k&auml;esoleva eeskirja paragrahvis 16 kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Confiscated items, substances and documents shall be handled pursuant to the procedure established in &sect; 16 of the Rules. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Kartserisse paigutatud vahistatu pakisaamise korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for delivering packages to persons in punishment cells </inglise>
<eesti>Kartserisse paigutatud vahistatule toodud k&auml;si- v&otilde;i postipakk v&otilde;etakse vastu, kuid antakse talle k&auml;tte p&auml;rast distsiplinaarkaristuse &auml;rakandmist. </eesti>
<inglise>Packages delivered by hand or by post to a person in a punishment cell shall be accepted, but shall not be handed over to him or her before the disciplinary penalty has been served. </inglise>
<eesti>VI peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter VI </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuse arestimajav&auml;line suhtlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Communication with Persons Outside Detention House </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamine arestimajas </eesti>
<inglise>Visitation in detention house </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialusel on &otilde;igus l&uuml;hiajalisele kokkusaamisele &uuml;ks kord n&auml;dalas, kestusega kuni kaks tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person has the right to receive a short visit of up to two hours once a week. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vahistatul on &otilde;igus l&uuml;hiajalisele kokkusaamisele &uuml;ks kord kuus, kestusega kuni kolm tundi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person held in custody has the right to receive a short visit of up to three hours once a month. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimajas viibimise ajal ei v&otilde;imaldata pikaajalisi kokkusaamisi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Long visits to persons held in custody in a detention house are not permitted. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamise tingimused </eesti>
<inglise>Visitation terms </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kokkusaamine toimub arestimaja territooriumil kokkusaamisruumis arestimaja ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja j&auml;relevalve all. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Visitation shall be conducted in the closed visiting room within the territory of the detention house and under the supervision of an officer or staff member of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kokkusaamisruumis v&otilde;ib arestialuse ja temaga kokkusaamisele tulnud isiku (edaspidi kokkusaaja) eraldada klaasist v&otilde;i traatv&otilde;rgust vaheseinaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the closed visiting room, the detained person and the person visiting him or her (hereinafter visitor) may be separated by a glass or wire mesh partition. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestialusele v&otilde;imaldatakse kokkusaamine korraga kuni kahe t&auml;iskasvanud isikuga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A detained person is permitted to be visited by up to two adult persons at a time. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamisele v&otilde;ib t&auml;iskasvanu kaasa v&otilde;tta lapsi. </eesti>
<inglise>Visiting adults may be accompanied by children. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamise taotlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Application for visitation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kokkusaamine toimub arestialuse v&otilde;i kokkusaaja kirjaliku taotluse alusel ja arestimaja juhi v&otilde;i tema poolt volitatud isiku loal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Visitation shall be conducted on the basis of a written application by the detained person or the visitor and with the permission of the head of the detention house or a person authorised by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kokkusaamise v&otilde;imaldamisel tehakse vastav kanne arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml;arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If visitation is permitted, a corresponding entry shall be made in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamise taotluses esitatavad andmed </eesti>
<inglise>Information to be submitted in application for visit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kokkusaamise taotluses m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An application for a visit shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) taotleja ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the given name and surname of the applicant; </inglise>
<eesti>2) isiku ees- ja perekonnanimi, kellega kokkusaamist taotletakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the given name and surname of the person requested to be visited; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui kokkusaamisele v&otilde;etakse kaasa lapsed, siis m&auml;rge selle kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if the visitor is accompanied by children, a corresponding notation; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kokkusaamisel suhtlemiseks kasutatav keel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the language intended to be used during the visit; </inglise>
<eesti>5) soovitav kokkusaamise aeg; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the requested time of the visit; </inglise>
<eesti>6) taotleja allkiri ja kuup&auml;ev. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the signature of the applicant, and the date. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kokkusaaja m&auml;rgib lisaks l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud andmetele veel ka j&auml;rgmised andmed: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In addition to the information specified in subsection (1), a visitor shall indicate the following data: </inglise>
<eesti>1) oma s&uuml;nniaeg ja -koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) his or her date and place of birth; </inglise>
<eesti>2) aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>2) address; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isikukood; </eesti>
<inglise>3) personal identification code; </inglise>
<eesti>4) isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi number ja v&auml;ljaandmise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the number and date of issue his or her identity document; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tema suhe arestialusega (perekonnaliige, s&otilde;ber, tuttav, elukaaslane jne). </eesti>
<inglise>5) his or her relationship with the detained person (family member, friend, acquaintance, cohabitee, etc.). </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kokkusaamise taotlus pannakse arestialuse isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application for a visit shall be included in the personal file of the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamise l&auml;biviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for visitation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Enne kokkusaamisele lubamist tehakse j&auml;rgmised toimingud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Before a person is permitted to a visit, the following acts shall be performed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kontrollitakse kokkusaaja isikusamasus esitatud isikut t&otilde;endava dokumendi alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the identity of the visitor shall be verified on the basis of the identity document submitted by him or her; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tutvustatakse kokkusaajale kokkusaamise korda; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the visiting rules shall be introduced to the visitor; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tehakse kokkusaajale ettepanek anda kokkusaamise ajaks arestimaja vastutavale hoiule asjad, mis ei ole arestialusele lubatud. </eesti>
<inglise>3) a proposal shall be made to the visitor that for the time of the visit, the items not permitted for detained person be deposited in the detention house at the liability of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Enne ja p&auml;rast kokkusaamist otsitakse arestialune ja kokkusaaja l&auml;bi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detained person and the person visiting him or her shall be searched before and after the visit. </inglise>
<eesti>L&auml;biotsimist teostab l&auml;biotsitavaga samast soost arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>The person to be searched and the officer or staff member of the detention house who conducts the search shall be of the same sex. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) L&auml;biotsimisel kokkusaajalt leitud arestialusele arestimajas keelatud asjad v&otilde;etakse hoiule ja tagastatakse kokkusaajale p&auml;rast kokkusaamise l&otilde;ppu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Items not permitted for detained persons in the detention house, which are found from a visitor in the course of a search shall be deposited, and returned to the visitor at the end of the visit. </inglise>
<eesti>Toimingu kohta koostatakse protokoll. </eesti>
<inglise>A report shall be prepared concerning such act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui kokkusaaja keeldub asjade hoiule andmisest v&otilde;i l&auml;biotsimisest, siis teda kokkusaamisele ei lubata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a visitor refuses to be searched or to deposit items, he or she shall not be permitted to a visit. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Arestialusel ja kokkusaajal on keelatud &uuml;ksteisele &uuml;le anda asju. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A detained person shall not hand over any items to a visitor, or vice versa. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kokkusaamisel suhtlevad asjaosalised kokkusaamise taotluses m&auml;rgitud keeles. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) In the course of a visit, the persons concerned shall communicate in the language specified in the application for the visit. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja ei valda seda keelt, kasutatakse t&otilde;lgi abi. </eesti>
<inglise>If the officer or staff member of the detention house is not proficient in the corresponding language, the assistance of an interpreter shall be used. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamise katkestamine </eesti>
<inglise>Interruption of visit </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimaja ametnikul v&otilde;i teenistujal on &otilde;igus kokkusaamine kohe katkestada, kui see v&otilde;ib ohustada arestimaja julgeolekut v&otilde;i sisekorda v&otilde;i kui kokkusaamisel kasutatakse muud keelt, kui on m&auml;rgitud kokkusaamise taotluses. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An officer or staff member of a detention house has the right to interrupt a visit immediately if it may endanger the security or internal procedure of the detention house or if a language other than the one specified in the application for the visit is used during the visit. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kohtumise katkestamisest kannab selle katkestanud ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja kohe ette arestimaja juhile, kes v&otilde;tab vastu l&otilde;pliku otsuse kohtumise katkestamise v&otilde;i l&otilde;petamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The officer or staff member who interrupts a visit shall report such interruption immediately to the head of the detention house who shall make a final decision concerning interruption or termination of the visit. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamine kaitsja v&otilde;i vaimulikuga </eesti>
<inglise>Visits from defence counsel or minister of religion </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kokkusaamist kaitsja v&otilde;i vaimulikuga korraldatakse selleks etten&auml;htud omaette ruumis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Visitation by a defence counsel or a minister of religion shall be conducted in a separate room intended for such purpose. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kokkusaamine peab olema vahetu, mitte l&auml;bi klaasseina telefoni v&otilde;i muu sidevahendi kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Visits from a defence counsel or a minister of religion shall permit direct communication and shall not be conducted through a glass partition via telephone or other means of communication. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kokkusaamist on lubatud j&auml;lgida, kuid mitte pealt kuulata. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Visits from a defence counsel or a minister of religion may be observed but shall not be overheard. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkusaamist ei ole lubatud katkestada. </eesti>
<inglise>Such visits shall not be interrupted. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>Eriolukord </eesti>
<inglise>Emergency situations </inglise>
<eesti>Epideemia v&otilde;i muu &auml;hvardava eriolukorra puhul, mis v&otilde;ib h&auml;irida arestimaja normaalset tegevust, v&otilde;ib politseiprefekt arestimaja juhi ettepanekul kokkusaamised kirjaliku korraldusega ajutiselt &auml;ra keelata. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of an epidemic or other imminent emergency situation which may disturb the normal functioning of a detention house, the police prefect may temporarily prohibit visitation by a written order issued on the proposal of the head of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Kirjade saatmine ja saamine </eesti>
<inglise>Sending and receiving of letters </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialuse kirjad saadetakse arestialuse enda kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The letters of a detained person shall be sent at the expense of the person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kirjade saatmine ja saamine toimub arestimaja juhi kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Letters are sent and delivered through the head of a detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Kirjavahetuse edastamine avatud ja kinnises &uuml;mbrikus </eesti>
<inglise>Communication of correspondence in open or closed envelope </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialune annab oma kirja avatud &uuml;mbrikus vahetult &uuml;le kirjavahetuse eest vastutavale arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajale, kes kontrollib &uuml;mbriku sisu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person shall give his or her letters in an open envelope directly to the officer or employee of the detention house responsible for correspondence, who shall inspect the content of the envelope. </inglise>
<eesti>Seej&auml;rel kleebib arestialune arestimaja ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja juuresolekul &uuml;mbriku kinni. </eesti>
<inglise>Subsequently, the detained person shall seal the envelope in the presence of the officer or staff member of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaitsjale adresseeritud kirjad v&otilde;ib arestialune arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i teenistujale &uuml;le anda kinnises &uuml;mbrikus, mida arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja ei v&otilde;i avada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detained person may hand letters addressed to his or her defence counsel over to an officer or staff member of the detention house in a closed envelope which the officer or staff member is not allowed to open. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kinnise &uuml;mbriku tagak&uuml;ljele peab arestialune kirjutama oma nime ja kirja arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i teenistujale edastamise kuup&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At the back of a closed envelope, the detained person shall write his or her name and the date of handing the letter over to an officer or staff member of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>Kirja v&auml;ljasaatmine </eesti>
<inglise>Outgoing letters </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;ljaminev kiri postitatakse kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul arestialuse poolt kirja arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i teenistujale edastamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>An outgoing letter shall be posted within three working days after the detained person has handed the letter over to an officer or staff member of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialusele saadetud kiri </eesti>
<inglise>Letters addressed to detained persons </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kiri edastatakse allkirja vastu arestialusele kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul kirja arestimajja saabumisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Letters shall be delivered to a detained person against signature within three working days after the letters arrive in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Otilde;iguskantslerilt arestialusele saabunud kiri antakse arestialusele allkirja vastu vahetult k&auml;tte viivitamata selle saabumisel ja suletud &uuml;mbrikus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Letters from the Legal Chancellor to a detained person shall be delivered directly to the detained person against signature immediately at the arrival of the letter, whereas the envelope of the letter shall not be opened. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Sidekanalite kasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Use of communications channels </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialune kasutab sidekanaleid oma kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person shall use communications channels at his or her own expense. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Telefoni ja muud sidekanalit on vahistatul &otilde;igus kasutada juhul, kui arestimajas on vastavad tehnilised v&otilde;imalused ja kui seda &otilde;igust ei ole kriminaalmenetluse huvides piiranud uurija, prokur&ouml;r v&otilde;i kohus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person held in custody has the right to use a telephone or other communications channels if corresponding technical conditions are available in the detention house and if such right has not been restricted by a preliminary investigator, prosecutor or court in the interests of criminal procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Sidekanalite kasutamine tuleb korraldada nii, et oleks v&auml;listatud eri kambritesse paigutatud vahistatute omavaheline sidepidamine v&otilde;i kokkusaamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Use of communications channels shall be organised such as to preclude communication or contact between persons held in custody in different cells. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestimajas telefonitaksofoni olemasolu korral lubatakse seda kasutada telefonikaardiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If there is a public phone in a detention house, it may be used with a telephone card. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Arestialusel, kelle telefoni kasutamise &otilde;igust ei ole piiratud, on lubatud omada telefonikaarti, mida hoitakse arestimajja hoiule v&otilde;etud asjade juures. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A detained person whose right to use a telephone has not been restricted is allowed to own a telephone card which is stored with his or her personal belongings deposited in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Kirjavahetuse ja sidekanalite kasutamise piiramine </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on correspondence and use of communications channels </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui arestimaja juhil on p&otilde;hjust arvata, et vahistatu poolt kirjavahetuse pidamine v&otilde;i sidekanalite kasutamine takistab kriminaalmenetluse l&auml;biviimist, teatab ta sellest kirjalikult uurijale, prokur&ouml;rile v&otilde;i kohtule. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the head of a detention house has reason to believe that correspondence or use of communications channels by a person held in custody hinders the conduct of criminal proceedings concerning the person, the head of the detention house shall send a corresponding written notice to the preliminary investigator, prosecutor or court. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Uurija, prokur&ouml;ri v&otilde;i kohtu taotlus piirata kirjavahetuse pidamist v&otilde;i sidekanalite kasutamist paigutatakse koos arestimaja juhi vastavasisulise otsusega vahistatu isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The request of a preliminary investigator, prosecutor or court to restrict the correspondence or use of communications channels by a person held in custody shall be included in the personal file of the person together with the corresponding decision of the head of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kirjavahetust, telefoni ja muude &uuml;ldkasutatavate sidekanalite kasutamist ei piirata, kui vahistatu suhtleb riigiasutuste, kohalike omavalitsuste ja nende ametiisikutega v&otilde;i kaitsjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Correspondence or use of a telephone or other public communications channels shall not be restricted if the person held in custody communicates with state agencies, local governments and their officials or the criminal defence counsel. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduste ja kaebuste esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Submission of petitions and complaints </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialune v&otilde;ib esitada suulisi v&otilde;i kirjalikke avaldusi v&otilde;i kaebusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person may submit oral or written petitions and complaints. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestialuse palvel antakse avalduse v&otilde;i kaebuse kirjutamiseks paber ja kirjutusvahend. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of a detained person, he or she shall be provided with the paper and a writing instrument necessary for writing a petition or complaint. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) &Otilde;iguskantslerile, riigiasutustele, kohalikele omavalitsustele ja nende ametiisikutele ning oma riigi konsulaart&ouml;&ouml;tajale adresseeritud avaldused ja kaebused v&otilde;ib arestialune arestimaja ametnikule v&otilde;i teenistujale &uuml;le anda kinnises &uuml;mbrikus, mida arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja ei v&otilde;i avada. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A detained person may hand petitions and complaints addressed to the Legal Chancellor, a state agency, local government or their officials or the consular officer of his or her country of nationality over to an officer or staff member of the detention house in a closed envelope which the officer or staff member is not allowed to open. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja teeb avalduse v&otilde;i kaebuse esitamise kohta sissekande arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An officer or staff member of a detention house shall record submission of a petition or complaint in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduste ja kaebuste edastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Forwarding of petitions and complaints </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Avaldused v&otilde;i kaebused arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; kohta edastab arestimaja juht politseiprefektile, kes vaatab need kohe l&auml;bi ja v&otilde;tab vastu asjakohase otsuse v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;rab asjaolude kindlakstegemiseks distsiplinaarjuurdluse, mille viib l&auml;bi tema poolt nimetatud ametnik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The head of a detention house shall forward petitions and complaints concerning the work of the detention house to the police prefect who shall examine the petitions or complaints immediately and adopt an appropriate decision or order a disciplinary investigation in order to ascertain the relevant facts, and the investigation shall be conducted by the official designated by the police prefect. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Avalduse esitanud arestialusele antakse lahenduse kohta kirjalik vastus seaduses etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaja jooksul ning selgitatakse edasikaebamise korda. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detained person who submitted a petition shall be notified of the decision made in the matter in writing within the term prescribed by law and the procedure for appeal shall be explained to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Riigi- v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutusele v&otilde;i ametiisikutele adresseeritud avalduse ja kaebuse edastab politseiprefektuur saatekirjaga, mille &auml;rakiri lisatakse arestialuse isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A petition or complaint addressed to a state or local government agency or official shall be forwarded by the police prefecture with an accompanying document a copy of which shall be included in the personal file of the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>Vajadusel selgitatakse arestialusele ametiasutuste kompetentsi. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary, the competence of administrative agencies shall be explained to the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Avaldus kohtule, prokuratuurile, &otilde;iguskantslerile ja Justiitsministeeriumile edastatakse politseiprefektuuri kulul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Petitions to a court, prosecutor's office, the Legal Chancellor or the Ministry of Justice shall be forwarded at the expense of the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduste ja kaebuste registreerimine </eesti>
<inglise>Registration of petitions and complaints </inglise>
<eesti>Kirjalik avaldus registreeritakse politseiprefektuuri arestialuste avalduste ja kaebuste registris. </eesti>
<inglise>Written petitions shall be entered in the register of petitions and complaints of detained persons maintained by the police prefecture. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Avalduste ja kaebuste vastustega tutvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Responses to petitions and complaints </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Saadud vastus edastatakse avaldajale hiljemalt kolme t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul selle saamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A response to a petition or complaint shall be forwarded to the petitioner not later than within three working days after the receipt of the response. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestialusele tutvustatakse vastust ning seej&auml;rel paigutatakse vastus tema isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A response shall be presented to the detained person and thereafter included in his or her personal file. </inglise>
<eesti>VII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter VII </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuse distsiplinaarne m&otilde;jutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary Sanctions Imposed on Detained Persons </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarmenetlus </eesti>
<inglise>Disciplinary proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarmenetluse viib l&auml;bi politseiprefekti korraldusel arestimaja juht v&otilde;i tema poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud ametnik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Disciplinary proceedings shall be conducted on the order of a police prefect by the head of the detention house or an official designated by him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Distsiplinaarmenetluse k&auml;ik protokollitakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Minutes shall be taken of disciplinary proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile kirjutab alla menetluse l&auml;bi viinud ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja. </eesti>
<inglise>The minutes shall be signed by the officer or staff member who conducted the proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Distsiplinaarmenetluse materjal lisatakse arestialuse isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The materials of a disciplinary proceeding shall be included in the personal file of the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestialuse &uuml;mberpaigutamisel teise kinnipidamisasutusse lisatakse tema isiklikku toimikusse &otilde;iend distsiplinaarkaristuse kandmise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a detained person is relocated in another custodial institution, a statement concerning service of a disciplinary penalty shall be included in his or her personal file. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Imposition of disciplinary penalties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkaristuse m&auml;&auml;rab politseiprefekt arestimaja juhi v&otilde;i distsiplinaarmenetluse teinud ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja ettepanekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A disciplinary penalty shall be imposed by a police prefect on the proposal of the head of a detention house or the officer or staff member who conducted the disciplinary proceeding. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Raske distsiplinaarrikkumise korral on arestimaja juhil v&otilde;i tema &uuml;lesannetes oleval ametnikul &otilde;igus paigutada distsipliinirikkuja eraldi kambrisse enne distsiplinaarmenetluse l&otilde;petamist, kuid mitte kauemaks kui 24 tunniks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of a serious violation of discipline, the head of the detention house or the officer acting in the capacity of the head has the right to commit the disciplinary offender in a separate cell prior to the termination of the disciplinary proceedings, but not for longer than 24 hours. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja teeb sellekohase sissekande arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An officer or staff member of the detention house shall make a corresponding entry in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Distsiplinaarkaristuse t&auml;ideviimine </eesti>
<inglise>Enforcement of disciplinary penalties </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Distsiplinaarkaristuse t&auml;ideviimiseks kartserisse paigutatud arestialust hoitakse kartseris &uuml;ksinda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A detained person serving a disciplinary penalty in a punishment cell shall be held in solitary confinement. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialune ei tohi enda juures hoida isiklikke asju ega toiduaineid, talle ei edastata kirju ega pakke, ei v&otilde;imaldata kasutada telefoni ega muud sidevahendit, kohtuda omaksete ega m&otilde;ne teise isikuga. </eesti>
<inglise>The detained person shall not have personal belongings or foodstuffs in his or her possession, shall not receive letters or packages, use a telephone or other communications channels or receive visits from his or her immediate family or other persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kartseris v&otilde;ib arestialusel olla vaid piibel, arestimaja sisekorraeeskiri, seep, hambapasta, hambahari, k&auml;ter&auml;tt, rull tualettpaberit ja naisarestialusel h&uuml;gieenisidemed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A detained person committed to a punishment cell may have in his or her possession only a Bible, the internal rules of the detention house, soap, toothpaste, toothbrush, towel, toilet paper; a female detained person may have sanitary towels. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kartserisse paigutatud arestialuse kutsumine uurija v&otilde;i prokur&ouml;ri juurde v&otilde;i kohtusse ei vabasta teda distsiplinaarkaristuse edasisest kandmisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Summoning a detained person committed to a punishment cell to a preliminary investigator, prosecutor or court shall not release the detained person from further service of the disciplinary penalty. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestialuse juures kambris olnud isiklikud asjad antakse arestimajja hoiule ning tagastatakse talle p&auml;rast kartserist vabastamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The personal belongings which a detained person kept in his or her cell shall be deposited in the detention house and returned to him or her after release from the punishment cell. </inglise>
<eesti>VIII peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter VIII </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimajast vabastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Release from Detention House </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Vabastamise korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Release order </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialuse vabastamisel tagastatakse isikule allkirja vastu arestimajas hoiul olnud raha, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid, dokumendid ja muud esemed, samuti kviitung aine v&otilde;i eseme kohta, mida ei tagastatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon release of a detained person, the money, securities, documents and other items deposited in the detention house shall be returned to the person against signature and a receipt shall be issued to the person concerning the substances or items which are not returned. </inglise>
<eesti>Allkirjastatud dokument k&auml;ttesaamise kohta paigutatakse arestialuse isiklikku toimikusse. </eesti>
<inglise>The signed document concerning receipt of the items shall be included in the personal file of the detained person. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vabastatud isikul on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda kirjalikku &otilde;iendit arestimajas viibimise aja kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person released from a detention house has the right to demand a written statement concerning the time he or she was held in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vabastatav isik peab rikkumatult tagastama temale arestimajas kasutamiseks antud voodivarustuse ja muu inventari. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person released from a detention house shall return undamaged the bedding and other inventory provided to him or her for use in the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhul kui isik on kahjustanud kambrit v&otilde;i nimetatud vara v&otilde;i selle h&auml;vitanud, tehakse talle ettepanek h&uuml;vitada tekitatud kahju vabatahtlikult (mille kohta v&otilde;etakse vastav allkiri) v&otilde;i n&otilde;utakse see temalt sisse seaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person has damaged or destroyed his or her cell or the aforementioned property, a proposal shall be made to him or her to compensate for the damage voluntarily (certified by a signature) or the damages shall be collected from him or her pursuant to the procedure prescribed by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kainenema paigutatud isiku kainenemisel &ouml;isel ajal v&otilde;imaldatakse tema soovil j&auml;&auml;da arestimajja kuni hommikuni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) At the request of a person taken into custody to recover from intoxication who recovers during night time, he or she shall be allowed to stay in the detention house until the following morning. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Arestimaja ametnik v&otilde;i teenistuja teeb arestialuse vabastamise kohta sissekande arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) An officer or staff member of a detention house shall record the release of a detained person in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>IX peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter IX </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja ametnikud ja teenistujad </eesti>
<inglise>Officers and staff members of Detention House </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametnike ning teenistujate &otilde;igused ja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Rights and obligations of officers and staff members </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimaja ametnikul ja teenistujal on kohustus teenistus&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisele asumisel ning teenistuse ajal j&auml;lgida kambrisse paigutatud arestialust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Officers and staff members of a detention house are required to observe detained persons in their cells upon assumption of official duties and during the service. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestimaja ametnikul ja teenistujal on &otilde;igus igal ajal ning kohustus v&auml;hemalt kord vahetuse ajal arestialune ja kamber l&auml;bi otsida, et leida keelatud ese v&otilde;i aine, hoida &auml;ra v&otilde;imalik p&otilde;genemiskatse ettevalmistamine ning arestimaja ruumi v&otilde;i inventari rikkumine ja l&otilde;hkumine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Officers and staff members of a detention house have the right to search a detained person and his or her cell at all times and are required to do so at least once during their shift, in order to find prohibited items or substances and to prevent preparations for escape and damaging or destruction of the rooms or equipment of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestialuse otsib l&auml;bi temaga samast soost isik. </eesti>
<inglise>A detained person shall be searched by a person of the same sex. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Keelatud aine v&otilde;i eseme leidmisel koostatakse protokoll ning aine v&otilde;i ese v&otilde;etakse arestimaja hoiule. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon detection of a prohibited substance or item, a report shall be prepared and the substance or item shall be deposited with the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Arestimaja ametnik ja teenistuja teevad l&auml;biotsimise ja selle tulemuse kohta kellaajalise sissekande arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An officer or staff member of a detention house shall record the time of a search and the results thereof in the work time journal of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Arestimaja ametnikud ja teenistujad tagavad arestialuste kambritest v&auml;ljaviimise ning nende liikumise saatmise arestimaja piires. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The officers and staff members of a detention house shall ensure that the detained persons are escorted when they leave their cells or move around within the territory of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Arestialune viiakse kambrist v&auml;lja, kui teda on vaja viia uurimistoimingule v&auml;ljapoole arestimaja ruume, uurimisruumi, kohtumisruumi, meditsiinit&ouml;&ouml;taja juurde, du&scaron;i- v&otilde;i pesemisruumi, tualetti, vanglasse, raviasutusse, teise kinnipidamiskambrisse v&otilde;i kui kamber tuleb l&auml;bi otsida, koristada v&otilde;i desinfitseerida v&otilde;i kui arestialust on vaja l&auml;bi otsida, konvoeerida v&otilde;i arestimajast vabastada. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A detained person leaves his or her cell if he or she is required to attend investigative activities outside the rooms of the detention house or to go to an investigation room, open visiting room, medical staff, shower or washroom, toilet, prison, medical institution or another cell or if there is a need to search, clean or disinfect the cell or to search or convoy the detained person or release him or her from the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Arestialuste j&auml;relevalvet arestimajas korraldab politseiprefektuur viisil, mis tagab "Vangistusseadusega" s&auml;testatu ja arestimaja sisekorraeeskirjaga etten&auml;htud n&otilde;uete t&auml;itmise ning &uuml;ldise julgeoleku arestimajas. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Supervision over detained persons in a detention house shall be organised by the police prefecture such as to ensure general security within the detention house and compliance with the provisions of the Imprisonment Act and the requirements prescribed by the internal rules of the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Arestimaja sisekorraeeskirja t&auml;itmise ja arestialuste julgeoleku eest arestimajas vastutab arestimaja juht. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The head of a detention house shall be responsible for compliance with the internal rules of the detention house and for the security of the detained persons within the detention house. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml; korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Work organisation </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestimaja ametnike ja teenistujate teenistus korraldatakse vahetustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The service of the officers and staff members of a detention house shall be organised in shifts. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;graafikud kinnitab politseiprefekt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Work schedules shall be approved by the police prefect. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestimaja sisekorraeeskirjas reguleerimata t&ouml;&ouml;kohustused m&auml;&auml;ratakse arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; juhendiga, mille kinnitab politseipeadirektor. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Official duties not provided for in the internal rules of a detention house shall be regulated by the guidelines for the work of the detention house which shall be approved by the Director General of the Police Administration. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;juhendiga kinnitatakse ka arestimajas kasutatavate dokumentide vormid. </eesti>
<inglise>The formats for the documents used in a detention house shall also be approved by the work guidelines. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja ametikohustused m&auml;&auml;ratakse ametniku v&otilde;i teenistuja ametijuhendiga. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The official duties of an officer or staff member shall be determined by his or her job description. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Politseiametnikud kannavad t&ouml;&ouml;l olles politseivormiriietust, koosseisulised teenistujad eraldusm&auml;rkideta politseivormiriietust. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) While on duty, police officers shall wear a police uniform and staff members shall wear a police uniform without distinguishing marks. </inglise>
<eesti>X peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter X </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja dokumentatsiooni s&auml;ilitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preservation of Documentation of Detention House </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Arestimaja dokumentatsiooni s&auml;ilitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preservation of documentation of detention house </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Arestialuste isiklikke toimikuid s&auml;ilitatakse kuni viis aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The personal files of detained persons shall be preserved for a period of up to five years. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Arestimaja t&ouml;&ouml; arvestuse raamatuid s&auml;ilitatakse &uuml;ks aasta p&auml;rast viimast sissekannet. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The work time journals of a detention house shall be preserved for one year as of the date of the last entry. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Arestialuste avalduste ja kaebuste registrit s&auml;ilitatakse &uuml;ks aasta p&auml;rast viimast sissekannet. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The registers of the petitions and complaints of detained persons shall be preserved for one year as of the date of the last entry. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kainenema toimetatud isikute raamatut s&auml;ilitatakse &uuml;ks aasta p&auml;rast viimast sissekannet. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The journals for recording persons taken into custody to recover from intoxication shall be preserved for one year as of the date of the last entry. </inglise>
